BASF Stops Sales Process of Leather Chemicals Unit, FTD Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-04-07T05:08:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/basf-stops-sales-process-of-leather-chemicals-unit-ftd-reports.html
BASF SE (BAS)  has stopped the sales’
process of its textile and leather chemicals unit after failing
to get an offer the company thought reflected its value,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing an unidentified
spokesperson for the German chemicals company.  Lanxess AG (LXS)  had been interested in the leather chemicals
operations, the newspaper said, citing unidentified people with
knowledge of Lanxess’s interest in the business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  